race.comment: Giving PERFECT PICTURE (8) another chance in what looks a very winnable affair. The fresh run was good and she's just had no luck in two runs since, shuffled right back at Seymour and again badly held up as the winner took off at Sandown Hillside last time, charging into second late. This doesn't look overly strong and with clear air she can atone. DOLLAR SHOT (5) has been below her best at her past couple but they've been in better company, tackling a G3 two back at Caulfield. Prior to that she'd won two in a row and coming back to this level can see her bounce back. ESPINHO (7) is going very well this time in, placing in his past three since a narrow maiden win. Won't need to improve much to be figuring prominently. SUPPOSE I DO (9) resumes. He can mix his form but has each way claims and goes well here. BARBARIC LAD (4) presents third up and can peak here from a better draw.
